
[1]polyhalite

   POLYHA'LITE, n. [Gr. many, and salt.] A mineral or salt occurring in
   masses of a fibrous structure, of a brick red color, being tinged with
   iron. It contains sulphates of lime, of magnesia, of potash and of
   soda.
